        "authorId" : "f87fe7d3-581c-4cb6-b17e-b807c6f2c789",
        "body" : "So if ANY node doesn't have a zone, we just give up completely and silently?  That seems harsh..",
        "createdAt" : "2021-03-03T06:45:46Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2021-03-08T23:38:14Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "f87fe7d3-581c-4cb6-b17e-b807c6f2c789",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "eb97fd4d-5c60-4f7b-a0cf-573461a689e4",
        "parentId" : "a825c0fb-de74-4591-8175-ef023f665f0a",
        "authorId" : "399a0f74-29de-4365-9ae5-f743ae5f278c",
        "body" : "We give up very quickly at this point. If any endpoint does not have a zone specified (controller) or if any endpoint doesn't have a hint specified (proxy) we bail immediately. Although I think we could set some acceptable threshold for unknown values here, I'm not sure what those thresholds should be.",
        "createdAt" : "2021-03-03T08:06:23Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2021-03-08T23:38:14Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "399a0f74-29de-4365-9ae5-f743ae5f278c",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "c8bea649-bf5e-480a-bf5f-84c21b39b090",
        "parentId" : "a825c0fb-de74-4591-8175-ef023f665f0a",
        "authorId" : "399a0f74-29de-4365-9ae5-f743ae5f278c",
        "body" : "I have been adding more logging in other places and will add some here to make this a bit more noticeable. I've thought about an event on the Service here but that could get noisy pretty quickly. Maybe events are reasonable when we can't determine the zone or cpu of a node, but not when we simply don't have enough endpoints to add hints?",
